org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api.stream

Interface ObjectOutput

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public interface ObjectOutput
extends java.lang.AutoCloseable
    An ObjectOutput is a minimal interface for writing arbitrary objects to a data sink.

    Please note that this interface is different from ObjectOutputStream in that it provides only a fraction of the methods and functionality. This interface is used to keep the dependency towards the externalization mechanism to a bare minimum.

    As this class extends AutoCloseable, instances of this class must be closed explicitly. However, the Java 7 try-with-resources statement may be used for doing so.
